# Project Intelligence - Portfolio Website

## User Preferences & Workflow

### Development Approach
- **Keep it Simple**: Single HTML file, no build process, minimal dependencies
- **CDN First**: Prefer CDN-hosted libraries (Tailwind CSS, Google Fonts)
- **Static Deployment**: No server-side rendering, pure static HTML
- **Modern Standards**: Use latest CSS features, semantic HTML5

### Design Philosophy
- **Professional First**: Clean, corporate aesthetic targeting recruiters
- **Subtle Animations**: Eye-catching but not distracting
- **Sky Blue Palette**: Primary color #0284c7 (Sky 600), secondary #e0f2fe (Sky 100)
- **Responsive Always**: Mobile-first design approach
- **Information Hierarchy**: Clear scanning path for busy recruiters

### Content Strategy
- **PM Focus**: Emphasize product management transition, not just engineering
- **Business + Tech**: Showcase dual competency (MBA + 5 years engineering)
- **Clear CTAs**: Direct calls to action for PM/APM opportunities
- **Credibility Markers**: Certifications, MBA, research, entrepreneurship (HC BYTES)

## Critical Implementation Paths

### Adding New Sections
1. Follow existing section pattern:
   ```html
   <section id="section-name" class="py-24 bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm relative z-10">
     <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
       <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-12 text-center text-slate-900">Section Title</h2>
       <!-- Content -->
     </div>
   </section>
   ```
2. Add navigation link in nav element
3. Maintain consistent spacing (py-24)
4. Use max-w-4xl or max-w-6xl container

### Modifying Animations
- All animations defined in `<style>` block in `<head>`
- Key animations: fadeInUp, float, gradient, hover-lift, pulse-glow
- Use delay classes: delay-100, delay-200, delay-300, delay-400
- Stagger animations for visual hierarchy

### Color System Usage
- **Primary actions**: bg-primary (Sky 600)
- **Highlights**: bg-secondary (Sky 100/200)
- **Text hierarchy**: text-slate-900 (headings) → text-slate-600 (body) → text-slate-400 (muted)
- **Borders**: border-slate-100
- **Shadows**: shadow-sm, shadow-lg, shadow-xl

### Responsive Patterns
- **Grid**: `grid md:grid-cols-2` for desktop two-column
- **Text size**: `text-5xl md:text-7xl` for responsive typography
- **Spacing**: `mb-6` mobile, increase for desktop if needed
- **Navigation**: `hidden md:flex` for desktop-only nav items

## Known Challenges & Solutions

### Challenge: Keeping Single File Maintainable
**Solution**: Clear HTML structure with comments for major sections, inline CSS organized by purpose (animations, utilities, custom classes)

### Challenge: CDN Dependencies
**Solution**: Accept trade-off for simplicity - no build process needed. Can self-host later if needed.

### Challenge: Contact Form Without Backend
**Solution**: Use mailto: link for now. If backend needed, consider Netlify Forms or similar serverless solution.

### Challenge: SEO for Single Page App
**Solution**: Add comprehensive meta tags, structured data, and ensure semantic HTML. Consider adding blog subdirectory if content strategy expands.

