## Tool Usage Patterns

### File Modifications
- **Preferred**: Use `edit_block` for targeted changes to index.html
- **Avoid**: Rewriting entire file unless major restructuring
- Always verify changes with user before multiple edits

### Testing Approach
- Use `execute_command` with `open index.html` to test in browser
- Can use browser_action for visual verification if needed
- Test responsive breakpoints: 320px, 768px, 1024px+

## Coding Style Preferences

### HTML
- Semantic elements (nav, header, section)
- Tailwind utility classes (long class strings acceptable)
- Self-closing tags where appropriate
- 2-space indentation

### CSS
- Inline styles in `<style>` block
- Organized by: base styles → animations → utilities → custom classes
- Use Tailwind config for theme customization
- kebab-case for custom class names

### JavaScript
- Minimal to none (CSS-only preferred)
- If needed: vanilla JS, no frameworks
- Inline in `<script>` tag at end of body

## Architecture Decisions

### Why Single File?
- Simplicity: No build process, easy deployment
- Performance: Minimal HTTP requests
- Maintainability: Everything in one place for small project
- Portability: Can send single file, works anywhere

### Why Tailwind CDN?
- No npm dependencies
- Just-in-time compilation
- Easy customization via embedded config
- Reduced development friction

### Why Static HTML?
- Portfolio doesn't need dynamic content
- Fast load times
- Easy hosting (free options available)
- No backend security concerns

